Cameroon’s Cocoa Output More Than Doubled in June, Board Says

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-07-28T11:31:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/cameroon-s-cocoa-output-more-than-doubled-in-june-board-says.html
Cocoa production in Cameroon,
 Africa ’s fourth-largest producer of the crop, more than doubled
in June, the nation’s Cocoa and Coffee Board said.  Output climbed to 6,840 metric tons from 3,200 tons a year
earlier, the board said in report e-mailed today from the port
city of Douala.  Production up to June 30 since the season started in August
came to 229,040 tons, according to the report. Output in the
2009-2010 season was 198,000 tons, the board said in August.  The West African nation’s exports for the month increased
by 16 percent from 4,785 to 5,547 tons, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
